16 issues, as well as Cancer Navigators, Inc., Board Member, general counsel, and two terms
17 as Chair of the Board; and
18 WHEREAS, Virginia assisted Dr. Matt Mumber in creating the legal framework for the
19 organization which has grown over the decades into what is now known as Cancer
20 Navigators, Inc.; and
21
22 WHEREAS, Virginia is dedicated to the effort of assisting cats and dogs in animal shelters,
23 particularly in rural shelters with few resources, and since 2017 has transported over 300
24 dogs and cats to rescues all over the southeast and has been a part of relay transports to
25 relocate dogs and cats all over the country to adopters and licensed rescue; and
26 WHEREAS, Virginia is a member of the Board of Trustees of the Georgia Conservancy
27 since 2018, serving as Chair of the Board for two years and as a member of the Executive
28 Committee.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body recognize Virginia Barrow Harman for her outstanding dedication
31 to the community, commend her as a recipient of the 2025 Heart of the Community Awards
32 Honor Recipient, and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued success.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
34 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
35 Virginia Barrow Harman.
